The incident took place at around 6:40 this evening. The Ekurhuleni EMS spokesman, William Ntladi told Daily Sun that an alarm was received stating that Carnival City hotel is on fire. "Brakpan and Benoni central fire stations backed by Tsakane fire station, all responded swiftly to the scene," said Ntladi. Ntladi said upon arrival, offensive fire suppression was conducted and flames knocked down. "Damping down was conducted and the scene declared safe," he said. He said investigation indicates that the fiberglass material from the outside entrance atrium caught alight suspected to have been caused by an electrical short circuit. Ntaldi also said fire fighters responded with a fleet of four fire engines and 24 personnel. "Fortunately, no casualties were recorded on the scene. Further investigation will be conducted by fire safety officers together with Carnival City's safety officials," he said.  Carnival city burning ?? @Abramjee pic.twitter.com/EEJKzzcilk 